1.)Type Selector:
h1{
    color:red;
}

2.)id Selector=> <h1 id="key"></h1>
=>this id will be unique  on that page cannot be used again and apply
to only one

#key{
    color:red;
}

3.)class Selector <h1 class="key (?)"></h1>
=>this is the class we can give this to anyone to style like h1 

.key{
    color:red;
}

4.)Pseudo class and Pseudo element

a:hover{
    color:red;
}

Pseudo element

p::first-line{
    color:red;
}

5.)Attribute Selector
=>you can also id or class here #nameofid[href..]
=>href link will have color red not any other href like facebook.com

a[href="https://google.com"]{
    color:red
}

6.)Universal Selector
=>used when debugging required
=>It will apply style on every element in html

*{
    color:red;
}

7.)Combinator Selector

i)Descendant combinatry(child at any stage)
=>here we gave space between two Selector

.key span{
    color:red;
}

ii)child combinatry (direct child)

.key > span{
    color:red;
}

iii)Adjacent combinatry(right after sibling)
=>it will select sibling which is next to him not others

.key + h1{
    color:red;
}

iv)General sibling combinatry (all sibling)

.key~h1{
    color:red;
}

v)Add Selector
General sibling (right after sibling)

.key,h1{
    color:red
}